# sealmd (Cursor)

A zero-dependency Node CLI for local document review. Full guide: see `AGENTS.md`
at the repo root — follow it. Quick reference:

Run the engine:
`node skills/seal-review/scripts/seal.mjs <command> --in <doc.md>`

Common commands:
- `init --in doc.md` — create the `doc.seal.md` sidecar.
- `comment --in doc.md --body "…" [--anchor "exact span"] [--suggest "replacement"] [--mention a,b]`
- `accept --in doc.md --id ID` — apply a suggestion to `doc.md`.
- `dismiss --in doc.md --id ID` — resolve a comment.
- `render --in doc.md --open` — build the review page.
- `start --in doc.md --open` — init-if-needed **then** serve (use this to launch; plain
  `serve` errors on a doc with no sidecar). Run it in the background and react to the
  `SEAL_EVENT` lines it prints — see AGENTS.md "live loop".

Always commit `doc.md` + `doc.seal.md`; `*.review.html` is generated and gitignored.
